children.name: In this section well walk through setting up a Component Set with multiple sets of properties. Here, we have a set of inputs which have different states (default, focus, error, etc) and two different types (input or select). The example is already set up with properly styled variants just like we did in the previous step, but we still need to name them.
children.characters:
In this section well walk through setting up a Component Set with multiple sets of properties. 

Here, we have a set of inputs which have different states (default, focus, error, etc) and two different types (input or select).

The example is already set up with properly styled variants just like we did in the previous step, but we still need to name them.

children.name: You might be wondering how Figma interpreted each property when we combined all of the components. When Components are named with forward slashes (usually to group components into a hierarchical menu), Figma will interpret the first group as the name of the Component Set. Each subsequent group is treated as a new property and its values are populated from all unique names at the same level.

When Components are named with forward slashes (usually to group components into a hierarchical menu), Figma will interpret the first group as the name of the Component Set. Each subsequent group is treated as a new property and its values are populated from all unique names at the same level.

children.name: What exists as a single component in code is often represented by multiple components in Figma. Variants can help you mirror that structure for improved alignment with your code base.((Variants enable you to: -> Associate different variations with a single component -> Map them to key/value pairs -> Improve inspect tab for devs
children.characters:
What exists as a single component in code is often represented by multiple components in Figma.

Variants can help you mirror that structure for improved alignment with your code base.((Variants enable you to:
-> Associate different variations
    with a single component
-> Map them to key/value pairs
-> Improve inspect tab for devs

children.name: Variants let you take individual components and combine them as variants within one overarching Component set. This can help make components: -> Easier to find in Assets panel -> Simpler to use -> Improve discovery of variations -> More aligned with code
children.characters:
Variants let you take individual components and combine them as variants within one overarching Component set.

This can help make components:
-> Easier to find in Assets panel
-> Simpler to use 
-> Improve discovery of variations
-> More aligned with code
